<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>WEEK 1 - DAY 1 (Education)</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        /* Splash Screen */
        .splash-screen {
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100vh;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            z-index: 9999;
            transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
        }

        .splash-screen.hidden {
            opacity: 0;
            pointer-events: none;
        }

        .splash-title {
            font-size: 4rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        .splash-subtitle {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #f0f0f0;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .splash-button {
            padding: 20px 60px;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            background: white;
            color: #667eea;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 50px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: bold;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
            transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
        }

        .splash-button:hover {
            transform: translateY(-3px);
            box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        /* Main Container */
        .container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            display: none;
        }

        .container.active {
            display: block;
        }

        /* Header */
        .header {
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .header h1 {
            color: #667eea;
            font-size: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .progress-bar {
            width: 100%;
            height: 30px;
            background: #e0e0e0;
            border-radius: 15px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }

        .progress-fill {
            height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            transition: width 0.5s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: white;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Vocabulary Section */
        .vocab-section {
            background: white;
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .vocab-toggle {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 15px 25px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            cursor: pointer;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            transition: transform 0.2s ease;
        }

        .vocab-toggle:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }

        .vocab-content {
            max-height: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
        }

        .vocab-content.active {
            max-height: 2000px;
            padding-top: 20px;
        }

        .vocab-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(450px, 1fr));
            gap: 15px;
        }

        .vocab-item {
            padding: 12px;
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .vocab-word {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #667eea;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .vocab-definition {
            color: #555;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        /* Task Card */
        .task-card {
            background: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            display: none;
        }

        .task-card.active {
            display: block;
            animation: slideIn 0.5s ease;
        }

        @keyframes slideIn {
            from {
                opacity: 0;
                transform: translateY(30px);
            }
            to {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateY(0);
            }
        }

        .task-header {
            border-bottom: 3px solid #667eea;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        .task-title {
            color: #667eea;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .task-description {
            color: #666;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        /* Break Screen */
        .break-screen {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 60px 30px;
        }

        .break-emoji {
            font-size: 5rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .break-title {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #667eea;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .break-text {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        /* Buttons */
        .btn {
            padding: 12px 30px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
        }

        .btn-primary {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
        }

        .btn-primary:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
        }

        .btn-success {
            background: #28a745;
            color: white;
        }

        .btn-success:hover {
            background: #218838;
        }

        .task-buttons {
            margin-top: 30px;
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        /* Answer Section */
        .answer-section {
            background: #e8f5e9;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            border-left: 5px solid #28a745;
            display: none;
        }

        .answer-section.show {
            display: block;
            animation: slideIn 0.3s ease;
        }

        .answer-title {
            color: #28a745;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        /* Input Fields */
        input[type="text"], textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 8px 0;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
        }

        input[type="text"]:focus, textarea:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: #667eea;
        }

        /* Question Styles */
        .question {
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            padding: 15px;
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        .question-text {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .options {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .option {
            margin: 8px 0;
        }

        /* PDF Embed */
        .pdf-container {
            width: 100%;
            height: 800px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        /* Video Container */
        .video-container {
            position: relative;
            padding-bottom: 56.25%;
            height: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .video-container iframe {
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
        }

        /* Audio Player */
        .audio-player {
            width: 100%;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        /* Grammar Box */
        .grammar-reminder {
            background: #fff3cd;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border-left: 5px solid #ffc107;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        .grammar-reminder h3 {
            color: #856404;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .grammar-reminder ul {
            margin-left: 20px;
            color: #856404;
        }

        /* Listening Note Completion */
        .listening-notes {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .listening-notes h3 {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .listening-notes ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .listening-notes li {
            margin: 10px 0;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .gap {
            display: inline-block;
            min-width: 200px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #667eea;
            margin: 0 5px;
        }

        /* Completion Message */
        .completion {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 40px;
        }

        .completion-emoji {
            font-size: 5rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .completion-title {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #28a745;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .completion-text {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .back-btn {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background: white;
            color: #667eea;
            border: 2px solid #667eea;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-btn:hover {
            background: #667eea;
            color: white;
        }

        /* Individual Answer Feedback */
        .answer-feedback {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-left: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            padding: 3px 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .answer-feedback.correct {
            color: #28a745;
            background: #d4edda;
        }

        .answer-feedback.incorrect {
            color: #dc3545;
            background: #f8d7da;
        }

        .input-wrapper {
            display: inline-block;
            position: relative;
        }

        /* Two-column layout for reading passage */
        .reading-split-layout {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 30px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .passage-column {
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-radius: 10px;
            max-height: 800px;
            overflow-y: auto;
        }

        .questions-column {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .passage-paragraph {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            text-align: justify;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .passage-title {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .passage-subtitle {
            text-align: center;
            font-style: italic;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #666;
        }

        /* Question styling for IELTS format */
        .ielts-question-group {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }

        .question-instruction {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .question-item {
            margin: 15px 0;
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .question-number {
            font-weight: bold;
            min-width: 30px;
        }

        .tf-options {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin-top: 8px;
        }

        .tf-option {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .tf-option input[type="radio"] {
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        input[type="text"].answer-input {
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            padding: 5px 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        input[type="text"].answer-input.correct {
            border-color: #28a745;
            background: #d4edda;
        }

        input[type="text"].answer-input.incorrect {
            border-color: #dc3545;
            background: #f8d7da;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Back to Dashboard Button -->
    <a href="../dashboard.html" class="back-btn">← Back to Dashboard</a>

    <!-- Splash Screen -->
    <div class="splash-screen" id="splashScreen">
        <div class="splash-title">WEEK 1</div>
        <div class="splash-subtitle">(Education) DAY One</div>
        <button class="splash-button" onclick="startLearning()">OK</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Container -->
    <div class="container" id="mainContainer">
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="header">
            <h1>📚 WEEK 1 - DAY 1: Education</h1>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill" id="progressBar" style="width: 0%;">
                    <span id="progressText">0 / 10 Tasks</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Vocabulary Section -->
        <div class="vocab-section">
            <button class="vocab-toggle" onclick="toggleVocab()">
                <span>📖 Daily Vocabulary (50 Words)</span>
                <span id="vocabArrow">▼</span>
            </button>
            <div class="vocab-content" id="vocabContent">
                <div class="vocab-grid">
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">1. studious</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">showing a strong tendency to spend time studying and reading</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">2. memorisation</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the process of storing information in memory without deep understanding</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">3. curriculum</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">all the subjects, topics, and skills that students are expected to study</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">4. collaborative</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">working together with others towards a shared goal</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">5. concentrate</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to focus your full attention on a task without being distracted</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">6. overcome</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to succeed in dealing with or controlling a problem</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">7. evaluated</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">tested, measured, and judged in order to decide how effective something is</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">8. postgraduate</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a person studying at a higher level after completing their first degree</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">9. distractions</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">things that prevent you from concentrating on what you are doing</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">10. scholarship</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a sum of money given to a student to help pay for their education</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">11. engagement</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">active participation and involvement in learning</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">12. critical thinking</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the ability to analyze information objectively and make reasoned judgments</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">13. repetition</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">doing or saying the same thing multiple times</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">14. dissatisfied</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">not pleased or content with something</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">15. traditional</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">following long-established customs or methods</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">16. pioneer</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a person who is among the first to explore or develop new ideas</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">17. influential</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">having great influence or impact on someone or something</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">18. philosophy</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the study of fundamental questions about existence, knowledge, and values</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">19. instruction</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">teaching or education; giving knowledge or information</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">20. passive</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">accepting or allowing what happens without active response</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">21. lectures</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">educational talks given to an audience, especially students</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">22. problem-solving</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the process of finding solutions to difficult or complex issues</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">23. laboratory</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a room or building equipped for scientific experiments and research</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">24. democracy</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a system of government by the whole population, typically through elected representatives</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">25. academic</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">relating to education and scholarship</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">26. revise</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to study material again in preparation for an exam</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">27. approach</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a way of dealing with or thinking about something</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">28. background noise</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">sounds in the environment that occur while doing another activity</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">29. equipment</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the necessary items or tools for a particular purpose</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">30. assignment</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a task or piece of work given to someone as part of their studies</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">31. disorder</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a disruption of normal physical or mental functions</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">32. dyslexia</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a learning difficulty that affects reading and spelling abilities</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">33. struggle</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to have difficulty doing something</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">34. environment</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the surroundings or conditions in which a person operates</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">35. preference</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a greater liking for one alternative over another</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">36. atlas</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a book of maps or charts</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">37. calculator</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">an electronic device used for mathematical calculations</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">38. protractor</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a tool used for measuring angles</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">39. compass</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a tool for drawing circles or measuring distances</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">40. prepare</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to make ready or get ready for something</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">41. notes</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">written records of information for study purposes</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">42. lecturers</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">teachers at a college or university</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">43. relatively</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">in comparison with something else; fairly</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">44. basics</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">the essential facts or principles of a subject</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">45. comfortable</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">providing physical ease and relaxation</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">46. complete</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to finish or bring to an end</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">47. various</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">different from one another; several</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">48. essential</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">absolutely necessary; extremely important</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">49. focus</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">to direct attention or effort toward a particular task</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vocab-item">
                        <div class="vocab-word">50. stage</div>
                        <div class="vocab-definition">a point, period, or step in a process or development</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Task 1: Mini Reading -->
        <div class="task-card active" id="task1">
            <div class="task-header">
                <div class="task-title">📝 Task 1: Mini Reading Exercise</div>
                <div class="task-description">Complete the text with the correct form of the verbs in the box.</div>
            </div>

            <div style="background: #f0f0f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <strong>Verb Box:</strong> concentrate, do, find, learn, overcome, prepare, study, revise, take, teach
            </div>

            <div style="line-height: 2; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                <p>Even the most studious among you will probably have difficulty studying at some stage in your academic career. If or when this happens, the only way to <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_1" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(1)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_1"></span></span> this problem is to go back to basics. First, make sure you have a comfortable environment to <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_2" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(2)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_2"></span></span> in. Some students need to have a quiet space to themselves and can't <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_3" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(3)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_3"></span></span> if there are too many distractions. Others need some sort of background noise, such as music or the company of friends. Whatever your personal preference is, you need to <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_4" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(4)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_4"></span></span> this first of all.</p>

                <p>Next, make sure you have all of the equipment or tools that you need. For example, if you are <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_5" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(5)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_5"></span></span> a geography course and you have to <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_6" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(6)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_6"></span></span> about countries and their capital cities then you will need to have your atlas to hand. If you're <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_7" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(7)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_7"></span></span> your maths homework then be sure to find your calculator, ruler, protractor and compass before you start.</p>

                <p>Perhaps you're not preparing a homework assignment or project, but are trying to <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_8" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(8)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_8"></span></span> for an exam. If so, you need to know exactly what is on your curriculum. You should also <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_9" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(9)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_9"></span></span> your notes and make sure that you have a clear understanding of what your lecturers have <span class="input-wrapper"><input type="text" id="q1_10" class="answer-input" style="width: 150px; display: inline-block;" placeholder="(10)"><span class="answer-feedback" id="fb1_10"></span></span> you. Of course, people with a learning disorder such as dyslexia may need to work harder than others at their studies as they often struggle to read even relatively simple texts.</p>
            </div>

